{"title_page": "Aspitates orciferaria", "text_new": "{{italic title}}\n{{Taxobox\n| name = ''Aspitates orciferaria''\n| image = Aspitates orciferaria.jpg\n| image_width = 200px\n| image_caption = \n| regnum = [[Animal]]ia\n| phylum = [[Arthropod]]a\n| classis = [[Insect]]a\n| ordo = [[Lepidoptera]]\n| familia = [[Geometridae]]\n| subfamilia = \n| tribus = \n| genus = ''[[Aspitates]]''\n| species = '''''A. orciferaria'''''\n| binomial = ''Aspitates orciferaria''\n| binomial_authority = ([[Francis Walker (entomologist)|Walker]], 1862) <ref>[http://mothphotographersgroup.msstate.edu/species.php?hodges=6717 mothphotographersgroup]</ref>\n| synonyms =\n*''Napuca orciferaria'' <small>Walker, [1863]</small>\n*''Aspilates orciferaria''\n}}\n'''''Aspitates orciferaria''''' is a [[moth]] of the family [[Geometridae]]. It is known from the polar region of the [[Ural Mountains]] and northern [[North America]].\n\n==Subspecies==\n*''Aspitates orciferaria orciferaria''\n*''Aspitates orciferaria baffinensis'' <small>(Munroe, 1963)</small>\n*''Aspitates orciferaria churchillensis'' <small>(Munroe, 1963)</small>\n*''Aspitates orciferaria occidentalis'' <small>(Munroe, 1963)</small>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q2317804}}\n\n[[Category:Moths described in 1862]]\n[[Category:Aspitatini]]\n[[Category:Moths of Russia]]\n[[Category:Moths of North America]]\n[[Category:Taxa named by Francis Walker]]\n\n{{Ennominae-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{italic title}}\n{{Taxobox\n| name = ''Aspitates orciferaria''\n| image = Aspitates orciferaria.jpg\n| image_width = 200px\n| image_caption = \n| regnum = [[Animal]]ia\n| phylum = [[Arthropod]]a\n| classis = [[Insect]]a\n| ordo = [[Lepidoptera]]\n| familia = [[Geometridae]]\n| subfamilia = \n| tribus = \n| genus = ''[[Aspitates]]''\n| species = '''''A. orciferaria'''''\n| binomial = ''Aspitates orciferaria''\n| binomial_authority = ([[Francis Walker|Walker]], 1862) <ref>[http://mothphotographersgroup.msstate.edu/species.php?hodges=6717 mothphotographersgroup]</ref>\n| synonyms =\n*''Napuca orciferaria'' <small>Walker, [1863]</small>\n*''Aspilates orciferaria''\n}}\n'''''Aspitates orciferaria''''' is a [[moth]] of the family [[Geometridae]]. It is known from the polar region of the [[Ural Mountains]] and northern [[North America]].\n\n==Subspecies==\n*''Aspitates orciferaria orciferaria''\n*''Aspitates orciferaria baffinensis'' <small>(Munroe, 1963)</small>\n*''Aspitates orciferaria churchillensis'' <small>(Munroe, 1963)</small>\n*''Aspitates orciferaria occidentalis'' <small>(Munroe, 1963)</small>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q2317804}}\n\n[[Category:Moths described in 1862]]\n[[Category:Aspitatini]]\n[[Category:Moths of Russia]]\n[[Category:Moths of North America]]\n[[Category:Taxa named by Francis Walker]]\n\n{{Ennominae-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Pvmoutside", "label": "safe", "comment": "Clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aspitates_orciferaria"}
