{"title_page": "Them vs. You vs. Me", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Them vs. You vs. Me\n| type       = [[Album]]\n| artist     = [[Finger Eleven]]\n| cover      = Fingereleventhemvs.youvs.me.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = March 6, 2007\n| recorded   = [[Chicago]], 2006\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Alternative rock]], [[hard rock]], [[funk rock]], [[post-grunge]]\n| length     = 40:24<br />44:36 {{small|(Canada)}}\n| label      = [[Wind-Up Records|Wind-Up]]\n| producer   = [[Johnny K]]\n| prev_title = [[Finger Eleven (album)|Finger Eleven]]\n| prev_year  = 2003\n| next_title = [[Life Turns Electric]]\n| next_year  = 2010\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Them vs. You vs. Me\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Paralyzer]]\n | single1date = February 28, 2007\n | single2     = [[Falling On]]\n | single2date = June 28, 2007\n | single3     = [[I'll Keep Your Memory Vague]]\n | single3date = October 2007 (Canada) February 5, 2008 (U.S.)\n | single4     = Talking to the Walls\n | single4date = March 2008 (Canada)\n}}\n}}\n'''''Them vs. You vs. Me''''' is the fourth full-length studio album from [[Canadian]] [[alternative rock]] band [[Finger Eleven]]. The album was initially rumoured to be titled ''Sense of a Spark''.  The album was released on March 6, 2007.  As of May 17, 2008, the album has sold 650,342 copies in the United States and has been certified Gold by the [[RIAA]].\n\nThe album won the 2008 [[Juno Award]] for [[Juno Award for Rock Album of the Year|Rock Album of the Year]].\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n|rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n|rev1score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"AM\">{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=r951574|pure_url=yes}}|title=Them vs. You vs. Me - Finger Eleven|last=Erlewine|first=Stephen Thomas|authorlink=Stephen Thomas Erlewine|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=August 9, 2011}}</ref>\n|rev2 = ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''\n|rev2score = C<ref name=\"EW\">{{cite magazine|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20014526,00.html|title=Them vs. You vs. Me|last=Willman|first=Chris|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|date=March 9, 2007|accessdate=December 7, 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n[[AllMusic]] senior editor [[Stephen Thomas Erlewine]] was conflicted with the album, praising the flourishes of disco-rock and funk in tracks like \"Paralyzer\" and \"Lost My Way\" but felt there wasn't enough of it in \"a collection of otherwise colorless but capable by-the-book alt-rock\", concluding with: \"So, the variety of rhythms, along with the increasing emphasis on acoustic-based power ballads, gives ''Them vs. You vs. Me'' the greatest musical variety of any Finger Eleven record, but they remain boxed in by their good intentions: they remain a group that's too polite to dislike but too well-mannered to remember.\"<ref name=\"AM\"/> Chris Willman of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' said of the band's change in musical direction throughout the record, \"Mostly, though, their newfound malleability results in cravenly radio-baiting ballads like \u201dI\u2019ll Keep Your Memory Vague\u201d \u2014 a title that may also describe listeners\u2019 reaction to this forgettable fare.\"<ref name=\"EW\"/>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| all_writing = [[Finger Eleven]]\n\n| title1 =         [[Paralyzer]]\n| length1 =         3:28\n| title2 =         [[Falling On]]\n| length2 =         3:07\n| title3 =         [[I'll Keep Your Memory Vague]]\n| length3 =         3:46\n| title4 =         Lost My Way\n| length4 =         4:00\n| title5 =         So-So Suicide\n| length5 =         3:15\n| title6 =         Window Song\n| length6 =         3:39\n| title7 =         Sense of a Spark\n| length7 =         2:55\n| title8 =         Talking to the Walls\n| length8 =         4:04\n| title9 =         Change the World\n| length9 =         3:46\n| title10 =         Gather & Give\n| length10 =         3:11\n| title11 =         Easy Life\n| length11 =         5:12\n| total_length = 40:24\n}}\n\n===Bonus tracks===\n#<li value=\"12\">\"Change the World [Acoustic Mix]\" - 3:43 (Canada and iTunes deluxe version)\n#\"Sacrifice [B-Side]\" - 3:45 (Canada, UK, and iTunes deluxe version)\n#\"Them vs. You vs. Me\" - 4:12 (Canada, UK, and iTunes deluxe version)\n#\"Falling On [Live]\" - 3:18 (Canada and iTunes deluxe version)\n#\"Paralyzer [Live]\" - 3:34 (Canada and iTunes deluxe version)\n\n==Chart positions==\n;Album\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Chart\n!Peak<br>position\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|2007\n|[[Canadian Albums Chart]]<ref name=\"billboard\">{{cite magazine|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=finger eleven|chart=all}}|title=Them vs. You vs. Me - Finger Eleven|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|[[Recording Industry Association of New Zealand|New Zealand Albums Chart]]<ref name=\"nz\">{{cite web|url=https://charts.nz/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Finger+Eleven|title=New Zealand albums chart|publisher=charts.nz}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|17\n|-\n|US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]<ref name=\"billboard\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|31\n|-\n|2008\n|[[ARIA Charts|Australian Albums Chart]]<ref name=\"aus\">{{cite web|url=http://www.australian-charts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Finger+Eleven|title=Australian chart positions|publisher=australian-charts.com}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|37\n|}\n\n;Singles\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Song (2007)\n!width=\"30\"|<small>[[Canadian Hot 100|CAN]]</small><br><ref>{{cite magazine|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=finger eleven|chart=Billboard Canadian Hot 100}}|title=Finger Eleven Canadian Hot 100 Chart History|magazine=Billboard}}</ref>\n!width=\"30\"|<small>AUS</small><br><ref name=\"aus\"/>\n!width=\"30\"|<small>NZ</small><br><ref name=\"nz\"/>\n!width=\"30\"|<small>[[Billboard Hot 100|US]]</small><br><ref>{{cite magazine|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=finger eleven|chart=all}}|title=Finger Eleven Hot 100 Chart History|magazine=Billboard}}</ref>\n!width=\"30\"|<small>[[Alternative Songs|US Alt.]]</small><br><ref>{{cite magazine|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=finger eleven|chart=Alternative Songs}}|title=Finger Eleven Alternative Songs Chart History|magazine=Billboard}}</ref>\n!width=\"30\"|<small>[[Pop 100|US Pop]]</small><br><ref>{{cite magazine|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=finger eleven|chart=Pop Songs B}}|title=Finger Eleven Pop Songs Chart History|magazine=Billboard}}</ref>\n|-\n|\"[[Paralyzer]]\"\n|align=\"center\"|3\n|align=\"center\"|12\n|align=\"center\"|7\n|align=\"center\"|6\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|align=\"center\"|5\n|-\n|\"[[Falling On]]\"\n|align=\"center\"|36\n|align=\"center\"|\u2014\n|align=\"center\"|\u2014\n|align=\"center\"|\u2014\n|align=\"center\"|31\n|align=\"center\"|\u2014\n|-\n|\"[[I'll Keep Your Memory Vague]]\"\n|align=\"center\"|12\n|align=\"center\"|\u2014\n|align=\"center\"|\u2014\n|align=\"center\"|\u2014\n|align=\"center\"|30\n|align=\"center\"|\u2014\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Finger Eleven}}\n\n[[Category:2007 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Johnny K]]\n[[Category:Finger Eleven albums]]\n[[Category:Wind-up Records albums]]\n[[Category:Juno Award for Rock Album of the Year albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Them vs. You vs. Me\n| type       = [[Album]]\n| artist     = [[Finger Eleven]]\n| cover      = Fingereleventhemvs.youvs.me.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = March 6, 2007\n| recorded   = [[Chicago]], 2006\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Alternative rock]], [[hard rock]], [[funk rock]], [[post-grunge]]\n| length     = 40:24<br />44:36 {{small|(Canada)}}\n| label      = [[Wind-Up Records|Wind-Up]]\n| producer   = [[Johnny K]]\n| prev_title = [[Finger Eleven (album)|Finger Eleven]]\n| prev_year  = 2003\n| next_title = [[Life Turns Electric]]\n| next_year  = 2010\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Them vs. You vs. Me\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Paralyzer]]\n | single1date = February 28, 2007\n | single2     = [[Falling On]]\n | single2date = June 28, 2007\n | single3     = [[I'll Keep Your Memory Vague]]\n | single3date = October 2007 (Canada) February 5, 2008 (U.S.)\n | single4     = Talking to the Walls\n | single4date = March 2008 (Canada)\n}}\n}}\n'''''Them vs. You vs. Me''''' is the fourth full-length studio album from [[Canadian]] [[alternative rock]] band [[Finger Eleven]]. The album was initially rumoured to be titled ''Sense of a Spark''.  The album was released on March 6, 2007.  As of May 17, 2008, the album has sold 650,342 copies in the United States and has been certified Gold by the [[RIAA]].\n\nThe album won the 2008 [[Juno Award]] for [[Juno Award for Rock Album of the Year|Rock Album of the Year]].\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n|rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n|rev1score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"AM\">{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=r951574|pure_url=yes}}|title=Them vs. You vs. Me - Finger Eleven|last=Erlewine|first=Stephen Thomas|authorlink=Stephen Thomas Erlewine|website=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=August 9, 2011}}</ref>\n|rev2 = ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''\n|rev2score = C<ref name=\"EW\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20014526,00.html|title=Them vs. You vs. Me|last=Willman|first=Chris|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|date=March 9, 2007|accessdate=December 7, 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n[[AllMusic]] senior editor [[Stephen Thomas Erlewine]] was conflicted with the album, praising the flourishes of disco-rock and funk in tracks like \"Paralyzer\" and \"Lost My Way\" but felt there wasn't enough of it in \"a collection of otherwise colorless but capable by-the-book alt-rock\", concluding with: \"So, the variety of rhythms, along with the increasing emphasis on acoustic-based power ballads, gives ''Them vs. You vs. Me'' the greatest musical variety of any Finger Eleven record, but they remain boxed in by their good intentions: they remain a group that's too polite to dislike but too well-mannered to remember.\"<ref name=\"AM\"/> Chris Willman of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' said of the band's change in musical direction throughout the record, \"Mostly, though, their newfound malleability results in cravenly radio-baiting ballads like \u201dI\u2019ll Keep Your Memory Vague\u201d \u2014 a title that may also describe listeners\u2019 reaction to this forgettable fare.\"<ref name=\"EW\"/>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| all_writing = [[Finger Eleven]]\n\n| title1 =         [[Paralyzer]]\n| length1 =         3:28\n| title2 =         [[Falling On]]\n| length2 =         3:07\n| title3 =         [[I'll Keep Your Memory Vague]]\n| length3 =         3:46\n| title4 =         Lost My Way\n| length4 =         4:00\n| title5 =         So-So Suicide\n| length5 =         3:15\n| title6 =         Window Song\n| length6 =         3:39\n| title7 =         Sense of a Spark\n| length7 =         2:55\n| title8 =         Talking to the Walls\n| length8 =         4:04\n| title9 =         Change the World\n| length9 =         3:46\n| title10 =         Gather & Give\n| length10 =         3:11\n| title11 =         Easy Life\n| length11 =         5:12\n| total_length = 40:24\n}}\n\n===Bonus tracks===\n#<li value=\"12\">\"Change the World [Acoustic Mix]\" - 3:43 (Canada and iTunes deluxe version)\n#\"Sacrifice [B-Side]\" - 3:45 (Canada, UK, and iTunes deluxe version)\n#\"Them vs. You vs. Me\" - 4:12 (Canada, UK, and iTunes deluxe version)\n#\"Falling On [Live]\" - 3:18 (Canada and iTunes deluxe version)\n#\"Paralyzer [Live]\" - 3:34 (Canada and iTunes deluxe version)\n\n==Chart positions==\n;Album\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Chart\n!Peak<br>position\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|2007\n|[[Canadian Albums Chart]]<ref name=\"billboard\">{{cite magazine|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=finger eleven|chart=all}}|title=Them vs. You vs. Me - Finger Eleven|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|[[Recording Industry Association of New Zealand|New Zealand Albums Chart]]<ref n