che]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 469\t \t\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 0.18%\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 0\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#ffe4e1; width: 3px\" |\n| style=\"width: 130px\" | [[Natural Law Party|Natural Law]]\n| [[John Hagelin|Dr. John Hagelin]]\n| align=\"right\" | 433\t\n| align=\"right\" | 0.17%\n| align=\"right\" | 0\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#A356DE; width: 3px\" |\n| style=\"width: 130px\" | [[Constitution Party (United States)|Taxpayers\u2019]]\n| [[Howard Phillips (politician)|Howard Phillips]]\n| align=\"right\" | 377\n| align=\"right\" | 0.15%\n| align=\"right\" | 0\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#FFFFFF; width: 3px\" |\n| style=\"width: 130px\" | Write-Ins\n| \n| align=\"right\" | 365\n| align=\"right\" | 0.14%\n| align=\"right\" | 0\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#FF00FF; width: 3px\" |\n| style=\"width: 130px\" | [[New Alliance Party]]\n| [[Lenora Fulani]]\n| align=\"right\" | 330\t\n| align=\"right\" | 0.13%\n| align=\"right\" | 0\n|-\n|-bgcolor=\"#EEEEEE\"\n| colspan=\"3\" align=\"right\" | '''Totals'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''258,506'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''100.0%'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''3'''\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{State Results of the 1992 U.S. presidential election}}\n{{United States elections, 1992}}\n\n[[Category:1992 Alaska elections]]\n[[Category:1992 United States presidential election by state|Alaska]]\n[[Category:United States presidential elections in Alaska|1992]]\n\n\n{{Alaska-election-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Main|1992 United States presidential election}}\n{{Infobox Election\n| election_name = 1992 [[United States presidential election]] in Alaska\n| country = Alaska\n| type = presidential\n| ongoing = no\n| previous_election = 1988 United States presidential election in Alaska\n| previous_year = 1988\n| next_election = 1996 United States presidential election in Alaska\n| next_year = 1996\n| election_date = November 3, 1992\n| image_size = x160px\n| image1 = George H. W. Bush presidential portrait (cropped 2).jpg\n| nominee1 = '''[[George H. W. Bush]]''' \n| party1 = Republican Party (United States)\n| home_state1 = [[Texas]]\n| running_mate1 = '''[[Dan Quayle]]'''\n| electoral_vote1 = '''3'''\n| popular_vote1 = '''102,000'''\n| percentage1 = '''39.46%'''\t\n| image2 = Bill Clinton.jpg\n| nominee2 = [[Bill Clinton]]\n| party2 = Democratic Party (United States)\n| home_state2 = [[Arkansas]]\n| running_mate2 = [[Al Gore]]\n| electoral_vote2 = 0\n| popular_vote2 = 78,294\n| percentage2 = 30.29%\t\n| image3 = RossPerotColor.jpg\n| nominee3 = [[Ross Perot]]\n| party3 = Independent (politician)\n| home_state3 = [[Texas]]\n| running_mate3 = [[James Stockdale]]\n| electoral_vote3 = 0\n| popular_vote3 = 73,481\t   \n| percentage3 = 28.43%\n| map_image = AK1992.jpg\n| map_size = 300px\n| map_caption = Borough Results\n{{legend|#f2b3be|Bush-40-50%}}\n| title = President\n| before_election = [[George H. W. Bush]]\n| before_party = Republican Party (United States)\n| after_election = [[Bill Clinton]]\n| after_party = Democratic Party (United States)\n}}\n\n{{ElectionsAK}}\n\nThe '''1992 United States presidential election in Alaska''' took place on November 3, 1992, as part of the [[1992 United States presidential election]]. Voters chose three representatives, or electors to the [[United States Electoral College|Electoral College]], who voted for [[President of the United States|president]] and [[Vice President of the United States|vice president]].\n\n[[Alaska]] was won by incumbent President [[George H. W. Bush|George H.W. Bush]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]]-[[Texas]]) with 39.4% of the popular vote over Governor [[Bill Clinton]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]]-[[Arkansas]]) with 30.2%. Bush won Alaska by a margin of 9.2%. Businessman [[Ross Perot]] ([[Independent (politician)|I]]-Texas) finished in third, with 28.4% of the popular vote.<ref name=results/> Clinton ultimately won the national vote, defeating incumbent President Bush. Alaska has only voted Democratic once, and that was in [[1964 United States presidential election in Alaska|1964]] for [[Lyndon B. Johnson]]. <ref>{{cite web|title=1992 Presidential General Election Results|url=http://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS/national.php?year=1992|publisher=U.S. Election Atlas|accessdate=8 June 2012}}</ref> It was also the last time a Republican only won the state of Alaska by a single digit margin of victory.\n\nWith 28.43% of the popular vote, Alaska would prove to be Perot's second strongest state after [[1992 United States presidential election in Maine|Maine]]. Alaska was also one of seven states to give a county to Perot. The others being [[1992_United_States_presidential_election_in_California|California]], [[1992_United_States_presidential_election_in_Colorado|Colorado]], [[1992_United_States_presidential_election_in_Kansas|Kansas]], Maine, [[1992_United_States_presidential_election_in_Nevada|Nevada]] and [[1992_United_States_presidential_election_in_Texas|Texas]]. Alaska awarded Perot [[Denali_Borough,_Alaska|Denali Borough]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS/stats.php?year=1992&f=0&off=0&elect=0|title=1992 Presidential Election Statistics|publisher=Dave Leip\u2019s Atlas of U.S. Presidential Elections|date= |accessdate=2018-03-05}}</ref>\n\n==Results==\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"\n! colspan=\"6\" | 1992 United States presidential election in Alaska<ref name=results>{{cite web|title=State of Alaska Official Returns November 3, 1992 General Election|url=http://www.elections.alaska.gov/results/92GENR/92genr.pdf|publisher=Alaska Division of Elections|accessdate=8 June 2012}}</ref>\n|-bgcolor=\"#EEEEEE\" align=\"center\"\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 15em\" |Party\n! style=\"width: 17em\" |Candidate\n! style=\"width: 5em\" |Votes\